BEFORE & AFTER: I designed the dreamiest bathroom for my home 🫶🏼 

I almost said “nah, pass” to this property BECAUSE OF THIS BATHROOM! When I placed the offer on my condo, I knew the bathroom had to be fixed and gutted out completely, which meant I had to invest even more on this place. The entire floor was a sinking ship and needed to be redone with new plumbing, tiles, and basically every single detail of the bathroom that you can imagine had to be changed. 

IDK whyyy, but I thought WHY NOT haha! This was the opportunity to take all the photos, pins, and ideas from my travels (thinking Bali) and turn them into action. Designing the most subdued & minimalistic bathroom for my own home. I knew I wanted a floating vanity, I knew I wanted stone-like features, and I knew I wanted smart-built-in features. And I’m so happy with how it turned out. I couldn’t have done it without the incredible team over at @iconremodeling (Don’t ask em’ how crazy I drove em’ haha!!)

I think the best part was that I got to design the entire thing. I even drew my vanity! This project was done with so much love, and I’m seriously SO happy with it! A big thank you to @daniklaric for helping me source the details! 🫶🏼

What do you guys think? 🤎

#bathroomremodeling #homedecor #remodelingideas #pinterest #pinterestaesthetic #pinterestgirl #beforeandafterhomeedition #chasingcarpediem #beforeandafter #apartmenttherapy

I’ll never take sound for granted again 🫶🏼 #lastweekendofaprildump

I haven’t written a lenghty caption in a long time, so I may be a little rusty here.
I wanted April to be showered by music, so I got my mum and I tickets to see Marco Antonio Solis live the very first day of the month, and let me just say, he was iconic. 
On that next day, I woke up with the headache of a lifetime. 
And you see, I’m the type to brush a lot of things off. Including a headache cos’ nothing a pill won’t fix right?
Somehow, that PCP appt I’ve been pushing got scheduled this month as well, because how many times can I call in to reschedule?
Complaining about how frequent my headaches were becoming to my doc and a few checkups later I was told that I had a hematoma formed and it was visible through the left side of my ear. 
And if you’re like me? you’re gonna google every little thing… so I’ll save you a search: It’s a blood clot caused by a broken blood vessel.
I think it’s only when they tell you bad news that you start to psych yourself to ‘feel it’ and I noticed the graveyard difference between listening through my left vs the right side of my face. 
Now, I don’t want to freak you out. And I know we come onto this app to share our happy moments, because no one wants to come and read about someone else’s problems right? This is not the case. I want to share this to remind you that 1) we’re all facing things that we we’re not ready to talk about and 2) you’re not alone.
I’m the same way, I like to talk about things after the fact.
So last week, I went in to drain out the hematoma. My audiogram came back that I did lose 4% of my hearing from my left side but hey, I can still rock it at concerts, so I’ll take it.

So this weekend, I did every little thing to celebrate sound. 

And this may have been a lot, but you guys are like my friends and I want to remind you to look after yourself <3 #aprildump #april

On my all-inclusive wellness retreat era bby 🌴🤍

Honestly, before this trip your girl was stressed. It’s the first time, in a long time, that I am trying to *balance* a personal life away from just working 24/7 and it turns out I’m dusty bestie. 

But you know, she’s trying to be a balanced baddie, so this invite to @unico2087 couldn’t have come at a better time in my life. Here’s what I learned about staying at a wellness retreat and why I 100% RECOMMEND THIS FOR YOU TOO!

✨ A beach staycation where you don’t have to leave anywhere? Yes please. Sometimes nature is all we need and it goes a long way to help you reset.
✨ Taking fitness classes early in the morning and having breakfast without rushing to your next task is next level.
✨ I haven’t met anyone who doesn’t like the spa, so take advantage and schedule a nice massage! Along with other ‘beauty experiences’ offered by the resort, I had a deep tissue massage and absolutely loved it.
✨ You don’t have to cook. I know we spend at least 50% of our day thinking what our next meal is going to be. I loved knowing I had options, and very healthy ones, to pick from for my dining experiences, because yes food is the key to our hearts haha.
✨ Relax. Relax. Relax. That’s it. 

If you’ve been to a resort you recommend, let me know! I’m ready to book my next one 🫶🏼 #myunicoexperience #rivieramaya

Beach, don’t be shady and join me on Saturday August 5th to be part of our first beach clean up in partnership with @shibumishade (!!!) 🤍🌊 

I am SO excited to host my first beach-clean up of the year with a the trailblazing lifestyle brand like Shibumi. The Shibumi Shade is 40% made up from Ocean-Bound Recycled Plastic. Shibumi’s mission is simple: Leave the beach better than you found it. 

And, to continue to the excitement I’m working with Debris Free Oceans once again. @DebrisFreeOceans is a Miami-based organization that inspires local communities to responsibly manage the lifecycle of plastics and waste as part of a global initiative to eradicate marine debris from our beaches, reefs, and oceans.

It brings me great joy to invite you all! We’re asking for all bodies, shapes and sizes to support the cause of a plastic-free beach. Put on your bathing suits and meet us at Virginia Beach on Saturday August 5th from 9 AM TO 11 AM. (Free Tickets on stories & on my bio!)

In the state of Washington, under a near constant cover of cloud and rain, there is a small town named Forks 🤍

Dream come true driving to Forks, Washington earlier this month. Here’s what you need to know if you want to do the *best* road trip evaaaa.

🏨 stay in Seattle (I stayed at @citizenm and loved it!)
🚙 the road trip to forks is 3 1/2 hours, but it’s actually A LOT of fun so time will pass rather quickly.
📍 first stop is near Port Angeles (where Bells & Edward had their first dinner!!) near it, you’ll come across the most beautiful lake ever. It was crystal clear.
🏔️ In between, you’ll cross so many beautiful scenic routes, definitely worth the stop.
🧛 When you arrive to Forks, you’re in Vampire town for sure — the whole town is in this universe(!!!)
🗺️ We drove to the chamber of commerce and the lady working the front desk was so nice she gave us a map with all the twilight locations from the book.
📖 We drove to forks high school,  Charlie’s police station, the cullens house, the swan house, Carlisle’s hospital parking spot, and lastly the museum (posted a TikTok about it!)
⚠️ We then drove to the treaty line, and there’s no exception. No vampires beyond this point. Only wolfs!
🍔 There’s a restaurant here called Three Rivers Resort heavily influenced by Twilight. I had a Vampire shake & the burgers were delish.
🌊 We continued all the way to La Push until we made it to Second beach… and there’s really nothing quite like it!

On our way back to Seattle, we took the ferry (car & all) and it cut our drive by a whole hour! SO worth it 🤍 let me know if you’re thinking about going!!#josstakesseattle #twilightroadtrip #octoberroadtrips

BEFORE & AFTER: The colorful-minimalist entryway of my dreams… Pinterest inspired of course! 🐚🌴💕

Putting together my entryway was no easy task; It was the last piece of my home that got completed. I wanted it to have a little more personality than the rest of the house, yet keep the simple, sea-side, minimalist aesthetics that carry the rest of my home. From purchasing my condo, I knew this entryway needed color, it was an empty white canvas, and I’m a Miami girl, color is in my DNA. So of course, the only thing that made sense was to build a forever bookshelf to the wall with a few of my fave books to color-coordinate the shelf.

I also wanted to add that coastal touch to it, and what better than an 80s flat art deco lucite table lamp? To pair it, I added a postmodern white laminate waterfall console table as well!

But that’s not all, the walls (though hard to see in the video) also needed a little love, and of course, there’s nothing better than lime wash paint from @jhwallpaint for that!

I love that this is the first piece of the house you see when you walk in… you feel right at home!
